Random walk Metropolis

\[ \begin{align} &p(Î¸ | data) \propto p(data | Î¸) \cdot p(Î¸) \\ &r_{M} = min\left(1, \frac{p(Î¸_{t+1} | data)}{p(Î¸_{t} | data)}\right) \end{align} \]

2 Generate data

Î¼, Ïƒ = 5, 2
y = rand(Normal(Î¼, Ïƒ), 500)
hist(y)

3 Define Likelihood and Prior

propÏƒ = [0.01, 0.001]
prior_Î¼ = truncated(Normal(0, 3), -10, 10)
prior_Ïƒ = truncated(Normal(0, 1), 0, 10)

function posterior(Î¸)
    ## prior 
    log_prior = logpdf(prior_Î¼, Î¸[1])
    log_prior += logpdf(prior_Ïƒ, Î¸[2])
    if log_prior == -Inf
        return -Inf
    end
        
    ## likelihood
    log_likelihood = 0
    for i in eachindex(y)
        log_likelihood += logpdf(Normal(Î¸[1], Î¸[2]), y[i])
    end
    
    ## unnormalized posterior
    p = log_likelihood + log_prior
    
    return p 
end
posterior (generic function with 1 method)

4 Run MCMC

n_samples = 20_000
burnin = n_samples Ã· 2
nchains = 6
nparameter = 2
accepted_Î¸ = zeros(nchains, nparameter, n_samples)
accepted = zeros(nchains)
Î¸ = zeros(nparameter)

for n in 1:nchains
    Î¸[1] = rand(prior_Î¼)
    Î¸[2] = rand(prior_Ïƒ)
    post = posterior(Î¸)

    for k in 1:n_samples
        
        ## new proposal
        proposal_dist = MvNormal(Î¸, Diagonal(propÏƒ))
        Î¸star = rand(proposal_dist) 
        
        ## evaluate prior + likelihood
        poststar = posterior(Î¸star)
        
        ## M-H ratio
        ratio = poststar - post

        if log(rand()) < min(ratio, 1)
            accepted[n] += 1
            Î¸ = Î¸star
            post = poststar
        end
        
        accepted_Î¸[n, :, k] = Î¸
    end
end

6 Trace plot and densities of the MCMC samples

6.1 With burnin

function trace_plot(; burnin)
    fig = Figure()
    
    titles = ["Î¼", "Ïƒ"]
    for i in 1:2
        Axis(fig[i,1]; title = titles[i])
        
        for n in 1:nchains
            lines!((burnin:n_samples) .- burnin, accepted_Î¸[n, i, burnin:end];
                color=(Makie.wong_colors()[n], 0.5))
        end
        
        Axis(fig[i,2])
        for n in 1:nchains
            density!(accepted_Î¸[n, i, burnin:end];
                    bins=20, 
                    color= (Makie.wong_colors()[n], 0.1),
                    strokecolor = (Makie.wong_colors()[n], 1),
                    strokewidth = 2, strokearound = false)
        end
    
    end
    rowgap!(fig.layout, 1, 5)
    fig
end

trace_plot(; burnin = 1) # keep all samples

8 Posterior predictive check

begin
    fig = Figure()
    
    Axis(fig[1,1]; title="Posterior predictive check")

    Î¼s = vec(accepted_Î¸[:, 1, burnin:end])
    Ïƒs = vec(accepted_Î¸[:, 2, burnin:end])
    
    npredsamples = 500
    ns = sample(1:length(Î¼s), npredsamples;
                replace=false) 
    
    minx, maxx = minimum(y)-4, maximum(y)+4
    nxvals = 200
    xvals = LinRange(minx, maxx, nxvals)
    pred = zeros(npredsamples, nxvals)
    
    ## calculate and plot each predictive sample
    for i in eachindex(ns)
        Î¼ = Î¼s[ns[i]]
        Ïƒ = Ïƒs[ns[i]]
        post_dist = Normal(Î¼,Ïƒ)
        
        yvals = pdf.(post_dist, xvals)
        pred[i, :] = yvals
        
        lines!(xvals, yvals;
                color=(:grey, 0.1))
    end
    
    ## mean of the predicted densities
    meany = vec(mean(pred, dims=1))
    lines!(xvals, meany;
            linewidth=3,
            color=(:red, 0.8))
    
    ## histogram of the data
    hist!(y; 
        normalization=:pdf,
        bins=25,
        color=(:blue, 0.3),
        strokecolor=(:white, 0.5),
        strokewidth=1)
    
    fig
end
